vpge research support fund page 1 overview stanford interdisciplinary graduate fellowship program sigf 2012 call for applications the office of the vice provost for graduate education vpge and the graduate fellowships faculty advisory committee gffac are pleased to announce the fifth annual competition of the stanford interdisciplinary graduate fellowship sigf program this university wide program awards three year fellowships to outstanding doctoral students engaged in interdisciplinary research sigf fellowships support stanford doctoral students to undertake novel cutting edge research and pursue questions that cross traditional disciplinary boundaries seventeen awards are anticipated fellowship terms the first two years of the fellowship provide an annual stipend $34200 for 2011 12 $8550 per quarter and tuition support 8 10 units for three quarters and 3 units in summer the third year provides 4 quarters of stipend tgr tuition and another $3000 stipend $750 per quarter to facilitate intellectual and professional development in interdisciplinary research recipients with tgr enrollment before the third year will also receive the $750 per quarter stipend sigf fellowships must be used within the first six years of graduate study at stanford application review process students submit an application in one of three categories 1 environment energy and sustainability 2 bio x biomedical research and biosciences and 3 a general submission category for all other interdisciplinary research interests student applications are reviewed by senior stanford faculty in each of the categories if needed applications will be moved to the category with the best faculty expertise for its review after faculty review the most competitive applications will be forwarded to gffac for final consideration applicants will be notified in late may 2012 eligibility and application guidelines current students in their first three years of graduate studies enrolled in any doctoral program or school at stanford may apply students with a nsf ndseg or equivalent fellowship are eligible to apply provided all that fellowship's support will be exhausted prior to autumn quarter 2012 2013 students should have demonstrated academic excellence and evidence of the potential for innovative research in an interdisciplinary area ability to link intellectual innovation with solving societal problems an interest in communicating research to a broader audience and a capacity for future leadership will also be considered as positive factors application information can be found at sigf stanford edu applicants must submit undergraduate and graduate transcripts curriculum vitae a research statement and 100 word abstract and two letters of recommendation from stanford faculty directions to complete the online application and for faculty to submit recommendation letters can be found at vpge stanford edu sigf sigf_apply html deadline march 15 2012 at 5 00 pm questions email sigf stanford edu o r call 736 0775 january 13 2012
